Here is indexes of zero in first level sorted index
After all it can look like this:
[0, 4, 12, 24, 40, 60, 84, 112, 144, 180, 220, 264, 312, 364, 420, 480, 544]
[0, 4, 12, 24, 40, 60, 84, 112, 144, 180, 220, 264, 312, 364, 420, 480, 544] = 0 + 4x + 4 * (x - 1) * x / 2
[4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 28, 32, 36, 40, 44, 48, 52, 56, 60, 64] = 4 + 4x
[4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4] = 4
[1, 7, 16, 29, 47, 68, 93, 123, 156, 193, 235, 280, 329, 383, 440, 501, 567]
[1, 29, 93, 193, 329, 501] = 1 + 28x + 36 * (x - 1) * x / 2
[28, 64, 100, 136, 172] = 28 + 36x
[36, 36, 36, 36] = 36
[7, 47, 123, 235, 383, 567] = 7 + 40x + 36 * (x - 1) * x / 2
[40, 76, 112, 148, 184]
[36, 36, 36, 36]
[16, 68, 156, 280, 440] = 16 + 52x + 36 * (x - 1) * x / 2
[52, 88, 124, 160]
[36, 36, 36]

S(x) = (x - 1) * x / 2
p(0, l) = [4*m1 + 4*S(m1), [1 + 28*m2 + 36 * S(m2), 7 + 40*m2 + 36*S(m2), 16 + 52*m2 + 36*S(m2)]_m1]_l =
 (0, 1, 1, 7, 2, 16)_l
+ (12, 28, 12, 40, 12, 52)_l * |l / 6|
+ (12, 36, 12, 36, 12, 36)_l * S(|l / 6|)

